  "body": {
    "view": {
      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<div class=\"contentLayout2\">\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"0d48416a-4a6a-4e74-b4e7-36d3e759af26\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Do you need help setting up <a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544541982/Depth+of+Field+in+Maya\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>Depth of Field in Maya</em></a> in Maya or using <a href=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/RFM27/pages/544542112/Tilt-Shift+in+Maya\" rel=\"nofollow\"><em>Tilt-Shift in Maya</em></a> controls?</p></div></div><p /><p>&quot;Bokeh&quot; is the name given to a side-effect of using Depth of Field where light sources or highlights form a shape where they are out of focus. The result is an almost &quot;glittery&quot; look that many people enjoy viewing.</p><p>In the below still from Pixar's <em>The</em> <em>Blue Umbrella</em> you can see light sources in the background have turned into circular blobs of colored light.</p><p /><a class=\"external-link\" href=\"http://www.pixar.com/short_films/Theatrical-Shorts/The-Blue-Umbrella\" rel=\"nofollow\"><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"The Blue Umbrella\" width=\"1280\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=535\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544542056/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"535\" data-width=\"1280\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542086\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"example_BlueUmbrella.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544542056\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"e66d9ada-07c5-4844-a0c6-73f048965c77\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1920&amp;height=803 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/example_BlueUmbrella.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=1280&amp;height=535 1x\"></span></a><p /><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-note conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"b1c2da8c-c597-43ae-9a62-7c83cb4d0447\" data-macro-name=\"note\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-warning confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>Did you know that Bokeh effects are from a topic in optics called the Circle of Confusion?</p></div></div><p /><p>They are available under the RenderMan Rollout in your camera Attribute Editor (AE) Panel.</p><p>These controls are called <strong>Bokeh</strong> in the menu.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" width=\"482\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/rfm_bokehControls.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=482&amp;height=680\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544542056/rfm_bokehControls.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"680\" data-width=\"482\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542089\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"rfm_bokehControls.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544542056\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"0e081c00-183f-4680-807a-7f3d4c8ef7b1\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/rfm_bokehControls.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=482&amp;height=680 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/rfm_bokehControls.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431579060&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=482&amp;height=680 1x\"></span><p>There are 4 controls and a convenient tooltip when you hover over the name or value fields. The controls from left to right and top to bottom are:</p><ul><li><p>Number of<strong> Sides:</strong> This determines the shape of the bokeh effect. If you choose fewer than three sides (triangle) the bokeh will be circular.</p></li><li><p><strong>Angle </strong>in Degrees<strong>:</strong> This controls the angle where sides meet for non-circular bokeh shapes (Number of Sides is greater than 2).</p></li><li><p><strong>Roundness: </strong>Values from 0 to 1 make the shape bow or flex outwards making it more rounded. Values from 0 to -1 bow inwards and make for sharper points.</p></li><li><p><strong>Density:</strong> This controls the brightness across the bokeh shape. 0 to 1 makes it brighter at the outer edge like a catadrioptic lens (look it up, quite interesting). 0 to -1 makes it brighter in the center and falloff towards the edges.</p></li></ul></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout two-equal\" data-layout=\"two-equal\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p>Below is an example using:</p><ul><li><p>Number of Sides = 6</p></li><li><p>Angle in Degrees = 33.33</p></li><li><p>Roundness = default (0.0)</p></li><li><p>Density = 1.0</p></li><li><p>Eyes on furthest alien = slightly creepy</p></li></ul><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"maya_AlienDOFTweak.jpg\" width=\"731\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"450\" data-width=\"731\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542077\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_AlienDOFTweak.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544542056\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"4b437380-5978-4562-8641-5dec1d45d464\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450 1x\"></span></div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p>Below is an example using:</p><ul><li><p>Number of Sides = 3</p></li><li><p>Angle in Degrees = 60.0</p></li><li><p>Roundness = default (0.0)</p></li><li><p>Density = -0.5</p></li><li><p>Eyes on furthest alien = less creepy</p></li></ul><p /><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" alt=\"maya_AlienDOFTweak2.jpg\" width=\"731\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-height=\"450\" data-width=\"731\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544542074\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"maya_AlienDOFTweak2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544542056\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"fe0fdffa-bc17-40f6-b037-7e60e0672714\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544542056/maya_AlienDOFTweak2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754431578816&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=731&amp;height=450 1x\"></span></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n<div class=\"columnLayout fixed-width\" data-layout=\"fixed-width\">\n<div class=\"cell normal\" data-type=\"normal\">\n<div class=\"innerCell\">\n<p /><p /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>"
    }
